cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the task of single image super-resolution using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of automated texture synthesis and adversarial training, which are also common techniques in generative models and deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents results on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in graphics (cs.GR).
